    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.19.7" />
                <note type="curatorial">Omaha Pub Lib</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">7</fw>
                <fw type="letterhead">
                JOHN G. NEIHARDT
                <lb/>
                BRANSON, MISSOURI
                </fw>
                <opener>
                <dateline>Dec. 26, '40</dateline>
                
                
                <salute>Dear Friends:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>What a fine-looking family, and what's better, fine as you look! Mona and I were genuinely pleased to have a look at all of you. Many thanks for remembering us.</p>
                
                <p>"The Song of Jed Smith" is nearing completion. Macmillans have wanted it for May publication, but any dead line would stop me. So it will definitely appear in Sept. I should be through in Feb.</p>
                
                <p>Mona and I made a lecture trip to Boulder and Denver in Oct., returning <del>up</del><add>down</add> the Platte to Wayne. Thought of you but had to hurry.</p>
                
                <p>We are both still impressed with the fine work you did on the biographical study. Too bad the State committee <unclear>flubed</unclear>! But, who knows? The thing may yet appear in complete form, <hi rend="underline">after</hi> the Cycle is out in a single volume.</p>
                <closer>
                <salute>Love to all of you!</salute>
                <signed>Jno. G. Neihardt</signed>	
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
        
